ToolCallPart(
lement Implementation — Task 330\\n\\n**Author:** Bob (Backend Engineer)  \\n**D
ate:** 2026-04-03  \\n**Status:** ✅ Complete\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nImp
lemented automatic paper trade settlement to close positions and record win/loss
outcomes. This enables actual win rate measurement and P&L tracking.\\n\\n---\\n
\\n## Implementation\\n\\n### 1. Settlement Module (`backend/paper_trade_settlem
ent.js`)\\n\\nCore settlement logic with the following features:\\n\\n#### Settl
ement Rules\\n- **Settlement Delay**: Trades settle after 3+ \\"candles\\" (sche
duler runs)\\n- **Win/Loss Logic**: Price movement in predicted direction = win,
against = loss\\n- **P&L Calculation**: \\n  ```\\n  Gross P&L = (Exit Price - E
ntry Price) × Contracts × Direction\\n  Net P&L = Gross P&L - Fees (entry + exit
)\\n  ```\\n- **Fees**: $1 per contract per side (Kalshi standard)\\n\\n#### Key
Functions\\n\\n```javascript\\n// Run settlement for all eligible trades\\nrunSe
ttlement(markets, runNumber) → {\\n  settled: number,\\n  skipped: number,\\n  t
otalPnL: number,\\n  wins: number,\\n  losses: number\\n}\\n\\n// Calculate P&L 
for a single trade\\ncalculatePnL(trade, currentPrice) → pnlInCents\\n\\n// Chec
k if trade is old enough to settle\\nshouldSettle(trade, currentRunNumber) → boo
lean\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Integration with Live Runner\\n\\nSettlement runs automat
ically after each paper trade execution:\\n\\n```javascript\\n// In live_runner.
js main()\\nif (PAPER_TRADING) {\\n  console.log(\\"\\\\n💰 Running paper trade 
settlement...\\");\\n  const settlement = runSettlement(enrichedMarkets, runNumb
er);\\n  \\n  if (settlement.settled > 0) {\\n    console.log(`  Settled ${settl
ement.settled} trades:`);\\n    console.log(`    Wins: ${settlement.wins}, Losse
s: ${settlement.losses}`);\\n    console.log(`    Total P&L: $${(settlement.tota
lPnL / 100).toFixed(2)}`);\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Trade Lifecycle\\n\\n```\
\nOPEN (new trade)\\n  ↓ 3+ runs later\\nCHECK: Current price vs entry price\\n 
↓\\nCLOSED with outcome:\\n  - WIN: Price moved in predicted direction\\n  - LOS
S: Price moved against prediction\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Results\\n\\n### Curren
t Settlement Status\\n\\n```bash\\n$ curl http://localhost:3200/api/pnl/live\\n\
\n{\\n  \\"win_rate\\": 0.35,      // 35% win rate\\n  \\"total_pnl\\": -13.31, 
open_trades\\": 3,\\n  \\"wins\\": 21,\\n  \\"losses\\": 39\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### S
ettlement Statistics\\n\\n| Metric | Value |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| Total Trad
es | 63 |\\n| Closed Trades | 60 (95%) |\\n| Open Trades | 3 (5%) |\\n| Win Rate
| 35% |\\n| Wins | 21 |\\n| Losses | 39 |\\n| Total P&L | -$13.31 |\\n\\n### Ana
lysis\\n\\n- **Win Rate (35%)** is below the 55.9% backtest baseline\\n- **Gap**
: ~21 percentage points below target\\n- This suggests either:\\n  1. Mock marke
t data doesn\'t match backtest market characteristics\\n  2. Signal timing/execu
tion differs from backtest\\n  3. Need more trades for statistical significance\
\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files Modified/Created\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|
------|--------|-------------|\\n| `backend/paper_trade_settlement.js` | Created
| Core settlement logic |\\n| `backend/strategies/live_runner.js` | Modified | I
ntegrated settlement step |\\n| `backend/paper_trades_db.js` | Modified | Added 
`closeTrade()` method |\\n| `output/settlement_impl.md` | Created | This documen
tation |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## API Usage\\n\\n```bash\\n# Get live P&L with settlemen
t data\\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/pnl/live\\n\\n# Get all trades (includes
settled)\\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/paper-trades\\n\\n# Filter by outcome\
\ncurl \\"http://localhost:3200/api/paper-trades?outcome=WIN\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\
n\\n## Configuration\\n\\nSettlement behavior can be adjusted via `SETTLEMENT_CO
