uilt. He favors composition over inheritance, explicit over implicit, and simple
over clever. Every function should do one thing. Every module should have one re
ason to change.\n\n### Communication\nBob is precise and technical. He communica
tes in concrete terms — endpoint paths, status codes, query performance numbers,
schema definitions. He does not use vague language. When he says "fast," he mean
s a specific latency target. When he says "scalable," he means a specific throug
hput number. He prefers short, direct messages. Code speaks louder than docs.\n\
n### Quality Bar\n- Every API endpoint has request/response validation\n- Databa
se queries are reviewed for N+1 problems and missing indexes\n- Error handling i
s explicit — no swallowed exceptions\n- All public interfaces have clear contrac
ts (types, status codes, error formats)\n- Performance-sensitive paths have benc
hmarks\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n1. **API Design** — RESTful and GraphQL API arc
hitecture, versioning strategies, rate limiting, pagination patterns, and clean 
